info-help-title = ReQuest - Command List

info-help-description =
    The following basic commands are available:

    {"-"} `/help`: This command.
    {"-"} `/support`: Prints an invite to the official ReQuest Discord.
    {"-"} `/invite`: Prints an invite to add ReQuest to your Discord.
    {"-"} `/ping`: Performs a basic connectivity test.

    The following enhanced-menu commands are available; use one to learn more about its sub-functions:

    {"-"} `/config`: Server-wide configurations, mostly relating to first-time ReQuest setup for your Discord. Requires "Manage Server" permissions to access.
    {"-"} `/player`: Functions for players to manage and view their player characters.
    {"-"} `/gm`: All Game Master functions. Requires a GM role to be configured for the server.
    {"-"} `/shop`: View and purchase items from the current channel's shop (if configured).

    The following commands are context-menus. To access them on the desktop client, right-click a user's name and choose "Apps". On mobile, view a user's profile and select "Apps" from the upper-right menu.

    {"-"} Trade: Give items or currency to another player.
    {"-"} View Player (GM-only): View another player's active character inventory.
    {"-"} Modify Player (GM-only): Modify another player's active character inventory or experience.
